ment of \u02bbAbdu'l-Bah\u00e1, An Analysis'']. New York: Universal Publishing Co, 1944. Reprinted. H-Bahai: Lansing, Michigan, 2004.\n*[http://www.h-net.org/~bahai/diglib/books/P-T/S/sohrab/SDP.htm ''The Story of the Divine Plan]. Taking Place during, and immediately following World War I''. New York: The New History Foundation, 1947. Digitally republished, East Lansing, Mi.: H-Bahai, 2004.\n*Ioas, Leroy, Mrs Lewis Stuyvesant [Julie Chanler] Chanler, and Ahmad Sohrab. ''Three Letters''. [11] leaves. New York: Caravan of East and West, 1954.\n*[http://bahai-library.com/sohrab_ferm ''Living Schools of Religion'']. Vergilius Ferm, ed. Ames, Iowa: Littlefield, Adams & Co., 1956. Chapter 19, \"The Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed Cause,\" by Mirza Ahmad Sohrab (pages 309-14)\n*[http://www.h-net.org/~bahai/diglib/books/P-T/S/sohrab/MBP.htm ''My Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed Pilgrimage. Autobiography from Childhood to Middle Age''].  New York: New History Foundation, 1959. Reprinted. H-Bahai: Lansing, Michigan, 2004.\n\n== Works about him ==\n*''Biographical Sketch of Mirza Ahmad Sohrab, Director of the Caravan of East and West, Inc''. 3. n.p. [New York?]: n.d. [1954]. Collins 12.10.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060619232333/http://theosophical.ca/PDF/Winter2000.pdf ''Light-Bearer Magazine: A Persian Rosary''], Winter 2000, pg 50 (reprint from ''The Theosophist'', 1978)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Covenant-breaker]]\n*[[Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed divisions]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://bahai-library.com/sohrab_ferm Biographical Notes]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://bahai-library.com/sohrab_vs_us-nsa_1941 United States National Spiritual Assembly vs. Mirza Ahmad Sohrab]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080829183129/http://www.h-net.org/~bahai/index/diglib/books.htm H-Bahai Baha'i Books \"Sohrab\"]\n*[http://bahai-library.com/momen_encyclopedia_covenant The Covenant, and Covenant-breaker]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sohrab, Ahmad}}\n[[Category:American people of Iranian descent]]